The paper deals with entailment problems and query answering, which are common topics in the database community (cs.DB). The use of powerful constraint languages such as guarded existential rules suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The restrictions on relations being transitive and linear orders suggest a connection to the field of discrete mathematics and specifically to the study of linear orders (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of decision problems, which is a topic often studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
